digiKam 8.8.0 - Release date: 2025-11-xx

*****************************************************************************************************
NEW FEATURES:

Bundles:         Update to last ExifTool version 13.32.
Bundles:         Update Qt6 based Linux AppImage to last frameworks Qt 6.9.1, KDE 6.16.0, ffmpeg 7.1, and OpenCV 4.12.
Bundles:         Update Qt5 based Linux AppImage to last frameworks Qt 5.15.17, ffmpeg 7.1, and OpenCV 4.12.
RawEngine:       Update internal Libraw to last 20250725 upstream.
Video:           Update internal QtAVPlayer to last 20250725 upstream (Qt5 only).

*****************************************************************************************************
BUGFIXES:

001 ==> 506429 - digiKam 8.6 DLNA server freezes after "upnp devices created: 0" (regression from 8.5).
002 ==> 506457 - The help window blocks digiKam at downloading AI models stage.
003 ==> 506577 - digiKam crashes after startup if database server is mysql 8.
004 ==> 506671 - Split single digikam database into core/thumb/faces/similarity dbs.
005 ==> 506712 - Two small note about the "New Advanced Search" menu.
006 ==> 506861 - digiKam crashes when trying to start scanning, if no album is selected.
007 ==> 507071 - Build failed with : error: ‘QString::QString(const char*)’.
008 ==> 507092 - Small fault in the Tooltip text.
009 ==> 507064 - Crash at start due to enabled video hardware acceleration.
010 ==> 479792 - In "digiKam Properties" sidebar, double quotes in caption are displayed as &quot;
011 ==> 507051 - Portable archive for 8.7.0 (digiKam-8.7.0-Qt6-Win64.tar.xz) is missing as a download option.
012 ==> 506663 - Face recognition finds nothing.
013 ==> 507101 - OpenCV 4.12 exception and face classifier not working.
014 ==> 507113 - Face recognition does not identify faces even after scanning hundreds of faces.
015 ==> 507299 - Typo: Settings tab is named "Behaviour" even when the locale is en_US.
016 ==> 507279 - Small typos and grammatical errors in the English text.
017 ==> 505199 - System shows 607MB RAM allocation that is not returned to the OS without a physical end task (or restart of system).
018 ==> 507190 - On Windows 11, digiKam background process remains running after app close.
019 ==> 506775 - digikam.exe process never closes after closing the window.
020 ==> 487911 - Tag but do not train.
021 ==> 479404 - Add delete button to People search filter field.
022 ==> 506073 - Automatic update doesn't work because no sha256 files on server.
023 ==> 468867 - Face detection and recognition.
024 ==> 446729 - Crashes with error: The Wayland connection broken. Did the Wayland compositor die?
025 ==> 507417 - Binary data seems gobbled by captions parsing.
026 ==> 503251 - Faces recognition stopped working.
027 ==> 507449 - Do not allow running multple instances.
028 ==> 507467 - Switching from lazy synchronization mode aborts remaining lazy sync.
029 ==> 507356 - Deleted 'Behaviour' term causes problem in language translation.
